Firebase
    - Project Settings > SDK setup and configuration > copy config 
        - go to project .src folder > create a file called firebase.js
        - install firebase dependencies
            - terminal
                - npm install firebase
            - firebase.js
                - import firebase from 'firebase';
                - pase the copied firebase configuration
                - initialize firebaseApp with the firebaseConfig from firebase library sdk
                - get the firebase db instance in firestore
                - get the auth from firebase
                - get the authentication sign-in provider instance
                - export the auth and provider as explicit exports
                - default export the db
    - Firestore
        - create database 
        - start in test mode
        - authentication > get started > sign-in method > enable sign-in providers
        - Firestore Database > Rules > Edit rules
            - remove this line request.time < timestamp.date(2021, 8, 4)
        - 
    - Login.js
        - import auth and provider from local firebase.js configuration into the functionLogin
        - use auth to sign in with the provider

    - channels
        - Cloud Firestore > Data > Start Collection > enter collection name
        - 


